  "prompt": "What is a teacher?",
  "response": "A teacher is an individual who facilitates learning, typically in a formal educational setting such as a school. Teachers are responsible for imparting knowledge, skills, and values to students through various instructional methods and approaches. They create lesson plans, deliver lectures, guide discussions, assess student progress, and provide feedback. \n\nIn addition to academic teaching, educators often play a crucial role in developing students' social and emotional skills, fostering critical thinking, and encouraging curiosity and a love for learning. Teachers may work with students of different ages and backgrounds, and their responsibilities can vary widely based on the education level (e.g., elementary, middle, high school, or higher education) and the subject matter they teach. \n\nMoreover, effective teachers often engage in continuous professional development to improve their teaching strategies and stay updated with new educational practices and technologies. Overall, the role of a teacher extends beyond instruction; it encompasses mentorship, guidance, and support in a student's overall development.",
